The article discusses how top Obama administration officials traveled across America to promote the clean energy economy. President Obama announced $2.4 billion in funding for advanced battery and electric drive projects. Energy Secretary Steven Chu visited renewable energy projects in Minnesota, while Secretary of the Interior Ken Salazar met with a solar panel company in Colorado. Other officials announced grants for companies in North Carolina, Florida, Missouri, and Pennsylvania. The week concluded with Secretary Chu and Congressman Ed Markey discussing clean energy jobs at Harvard University.